
Arithmetical Operators
+
-
*
/
^

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Comparison Operators

=
<>
<
<=
>
>=

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Logical Operators

AND
OR
NOT

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Constants

PI

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Labels

Labels must start with and underscore and contain at least one character (alphanumericals)
_start, _End, _loop5 and _a are valid labels.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Functions

ABS(arg)
Returns the absolute value of arg
Examples:
ABS(-3) returns 3
ABS(8) returns 8
ABS(1.5-7) returns 5.5

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

ATN(arg)
Returns the arctangent of arg
Examples:
ATN(0) returns 0
ATN(PI) returns 1.262626...

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

COS(arg)
Returns the cosinus of arg
Examples:
COS(0) returns 1
COS(PI/2) returns 0
COS(PI) returns -1

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

EXP(arg)
Returns the result of e^arg
Examples:
EXP(0) returns 1
EXP(1) returns 2.718281... 

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

INT(arg)
Returns the integer part of a number
Examples:
INT(3) returns 3
INT(3.2) returns 3
INT(3.8) returns 3

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

LOG(arg)
Returns the result of ln(arg)
Examples:
LOG(1) returns 0
LOG(EXP(10)) returns 10

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

RND(arg)
Returns a random number between 0 and arg (exclusive).
Example:
RND(arg) returns a random integer between 0 and arg.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

SIN(arg)
Returns the sinus of arg
Examples:
SIN(0) returns 0.
SIN(3*PI) returns -1.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

SQR(arg)
Returns the squareroot of arg.
Examples:
SQR(4) returns 2.
SQR(2*8) returns 4.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

TAN(arg)
Returns the tangeant of arg
Example:
TAN(PI) returns 0

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

PGCD(arg1,arg2)
Returns the PGCD between the 2 arguments
Example:
PGDC(25,5) returns 5

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Variable initialization and assignement

(LET) var = value
If var has not been declared yet, creates a new variable called var.
Otherwise, assign value to var (the new value has to have the same type as the previous value).
Examples:
foo = 1;
PRINT(foo);
foo = 5
PRINT(foo)
Will print 1 and 5 on the console.

bar = "Hello.";
bar = 12
Will throw an error.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

DIM array (d1_size, d2_size, ..., dn_size)
Creates a n dimension array where the ith subarray has room for di_size elements.
An array can only contain one type of data (integer, real, string, array).
Example:
DIM arr (10, 10)
FOR i = 0 TO 10
FOR j = 0 TO 10
arr(i, j) = 0;
FEND
FEND
Creates a 10 by 10 2D array and fills it with zeroes. 

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Commands

PRINT(arg1, arg2, ..., argn) 
PRINT(arg1 : arg2 : ... : argn)
Prints the given list of arguments on the console.
If an argument is followed by a comma, a newline will also be printed.
This can be avoided by using a colon instead.
Examples:
PRINT(10*3+5) 
35.

PRINT("Hello, " : "World!" , "This is a newline")
Hello, World!
This is a newline

x = 64;
PRINT("The squareroot of " : x : " is " : SQRT(x) : ".")
The squareroot of 64 is 8.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

INPUT(arg1, arg2, ..., argn)
Takes n inputs from the user and saves the value of the ith input into the ith variable.
Examples:
name = "";
age = 0;
PRINT("Enter your name and age:");
INPUT(name, age);

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

SPC(n)
Prints n spaces on the console.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

GOTO(label)
Jumps to the given label.
Examples:
PRINT(1);
GOTO (_end);
PRINT(2);
_end:
PRINT(3)
will output
1
3

_start:
PRINT("Home Sweet Home.");
GOTO _start
will output "Home Sweet Home" indefinitely.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

GOSUB(label)
Jumps to the given label. Execution will resume from this point after RETURN has been reached.
Examples:
x = 2;
GOSUB(_squared);
PRINT(x);
END;
_squared:
x = x * x;
RETURN
will output 4.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------



END
Halts the execution of the program
